<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="ctime" id="ctime">ctime</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntaxe :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;ctime&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy2">*</span><span class="kw3">ctime</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">const</span> <span class="kw4">time_t</span> <span class="sy2">*</span><span class="kw3">time</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
La fonction <code>ctime()</code> convertit le temps UNIX en une chaîne de caractères
au format :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">     jours mois date heures<span class="sy4">:</span>minutes<span class="sy4">:</span>secondes années</pre>
<p>
Utiliser <code>ctime()</code> est équivalent à faire :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">     <span class="kw3">asctime</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw3">localtime</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span>tp<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
